        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: convert HTML tables to code blocks for Telegram delivery (#94317)",
        "body": "## Description\n\nTelegram Bot API HTML mode does not support `<table>`, `<tr>`, `<td>`, or `<th>` tags. When agent output contains raw HTML table markup, it gets escaped as `&lt;table&gt;` and shows unreadable entity characters.\n\nThis change adds a preprocessing step that detects HTML `<table>` blocks in markdown input and converts them to pipe-formatted code blocks before they reach the markdown parser.\n\n## Changes\n- **`extensions/telegram/src/format.ts`**: Added `convertHtmlTableToPreformatted()` preprocessor; updated `markdownToTelegramHtml()` and `markdownToTelegramChunks()` to use it\n- **`extensions/telegram/src/format.test.ts`**: Added 3 new tests for HTML table conversion\n\n## Related Issue\nFixes #94317\n\n## AI Assistance\nThis PR was created with assistance from AI (Claude Code).\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Environment\n- Platform: Linux x86_64, Node.js v22.22.0\n- Branch: fix/telegram-html-table-escaping-94317\n\n### Evidence\n\nTest 1 - Simple HTML table:\n```\nInput:  <table><tr><th>Name</th><th>Age</th></tr><tr><td>Alice</td><td>30</td></tr></table>\nOutput: | Name | Age |\n        | --- | --- |\n        | Alice | 30 |\n```\n✅ Readable pipe table - no `&lt;table&gt;` escaped entities\n\nTest 2 - With thead/tbody: Header separator preserved.\nTest 3 - Existing HTML escape still works.\n\nUnit tests: 23/23 pass.\n\n### What was not tested\nFull integration test with a configured Telegram bot.",
